@Iampsv1 I blame us English teachers for hammering in that "repetition is bad" 😄

We really just mean "Don't start every sentence like 'He...', 'He...', 'Then he...'" 😄

@Iampsv1 You know, maybe JM is "the blond" to JK when he sees him for the first time next to a dark-haired friend at the club, but once they know each other, he's JM to him, not "the blond" (which makes JM seem like a stranger to the reader as well).

@Iampsv1 It's common in fics, but for anyone who wants to write outside of that and not get cut down by editors, I think it's good to consider how the characters would think about each other, rather than the "audience".

It's Christmas Eve, the biggest day of celebration for Swedes, and when I was the only one awake at 5 in the morning, watching new snow settle, my mind began quoting this poem and I had to share 🥰

🌲 Midwinter Greetings from Sweden🌲

Passing this book around and reading this beloved poem out loud together is a Christmas tradition in my family, and I wanted to "read" it to you as well ❤️ https://t.co/DAzvS660mX

"Tomten" (The House Gnome), 1881 ~ a poem by Viktor Rydberg

Translated from Swedish in 1926

Midwinter's nightly frost is hard
Brightly the stars are beaming
Fast asleep is the lonely yard 
All till morn will be dreaming

Faint is the moon, and snow-drifts shine
Glistening white, on fir and pine
Covers on rooflets making
None but the house gnome is waking https://t.co/G5lyJRGPJv

Mute is the wold, is nature all
Life is so frozen and dreary
From afar, but the rapid's call
Murmuring, sounds so weary

The house gnome listens, half in a dream
Fancies he hears the vital stream
Wonders whither it's going
Whence its waters are flowing https://t.co/f0kPzT2H6W

Then she'll twitter, sing and chat
Much of her airy travel
Nothing though of the riddle that
The house gnome can never unravel

Through a chink in the hay shed wall
Lustrous moonbeams on the house gnome fall
Upon his beard they're blinking
The house gnome's brooding and thinking https://t.co/Mp8P3a6izm

The house gnome goes to the hay shed loft
There, is his haunt and hollow
Deep in the sweet-smelling hay, aloft
Near the nest of the swallow

Empty, now, is the swallowed nest
But when spring is in blossom dressed
She for home will be yearning
Will, with her mate, be returning https://t.co/diB1hrrzmq

Thus he has seen them, sire and son
Endless numbers of races
Whence are they coming, one by one
All the slumbering faces?

Mortals succeeding mortals, there
Flourished, and aged, and went - but where?
Oh, this riddle, revolving
He will never cease solving! https://t.co/sJ3k4CdWpb

Lastly, the house gnome will steal to see
The masterfolks, loved so dearly
Long have they liked his industry 
Now, they honour him, clearly

Stealing on tiptoe, soon he nears
Nursery cots, the little dears
None must grudge him the pleasure
This is his greatest pleasure https://t.co/UkQFcsTJ3P

The dog, in kennel, so brave and hale
Wakes up and gladly wags his tail
The dog, he knows his brother
Watchman - they love each other https://t.co/8JdeHxc0zG

Goes to the hens, where the cock will sleep
Perched, with vanity teeming https://t.co/0lIwk2uP6i

The house gnome goes to the lambs and sheep
See! They are all a-dreaming! https://t.co/tDWE4a2Hud

Heedless of harness and whip and team
The horse, stabled, too has a dream
Manger and crib, all over
Fill with sweet-smelling clover https://t.co/OvaJD5pstu

Goes to the larder and tool house fine
Every padlock trying
See! By moonlight, in stalls, the kine
Dreaming of summer are lying https://t.co/LAlicNy91R

Runs his hand through his hair and beard
Gravely, his head a-shaking 
"Harder riddle I never heard
Vainly, my head I'm breaking"

Chasing then, as his wont for aye 
Such unsolvable things away
The house gnome trips, without hustling
Now, about duty bustling https://t.co/qBRy5afwq3

Grey, he stands by the byre door
Grey, in the snow appearing
Looks, as ever he did before
Up, at the moonlight peering

Looks at the wood, where the pine and fir
Stand round the farm, and never stir
Broods on an unavailing 
riddle, forever failing https://t.co/NKHvYAmJyT
